Unlike large retailers, we keep our costs low by using our suppliers’ inventories to supplement our inventory. 280,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1890280,For Sale:  Ammo at NORMAL prices.,"Downtown, Northern Lower Peninsula, Michigan",$ 10,"Listed On: Wednesday, July 17, 2013",Ammo,no type,no type,no type,no type,"First, start flagging these gougers on here as a scam because that is what they are.

If you are trying to find ammo at normal prices, it is not that hard.  I have been having the best luck for ammo at Walmart.  In the past week I have used the following method to buy 3,000 rounds of .22lr for $140.  First, call you local Walmart and find out  what time they are usually putting out their trucks.  Go to ammo-can.net  (site has been running really slow the last week) about two hours before that time and search by state and caliber for what you are looking for, check the box that says ""include out of stock items"". Scroll through the list until you find the store you want to check and click on ""force check"".  This will check inventory for that store for all calibers.  It will show in stock about 2 hours before they put it on the shelf.  You may have to get there early and wait in line.  You may also want to ask your local store if they usually have a line waiting and what time people get there to wait.  My local store in Traverse City gets their trucks around 4pm and the stock goes on the shelves around 6pm.  Ammo-can.net will show in stock for my store between 4-5.  I have been able to get more ammo than I need doing this and haven't paid over retail yet.  If you look at most of the ammo on here, it is from Walmart, this is what these scammers are doing and reselling to you at a 100% profit.
Also, freedommunitions.com has most calibers in stock(no .22lr).  Go to their website and click on the link ""in stock now"" on the left.  Earlier they had 9, 40, 45, 38, 380, 223 etc.
Gunbot.net is another useful tool.  They have been showing .22lr available from 7 cents per round on up today.  Still not the best deal but better than armslist.com gougers."

You've been asking for a couple +P 45 AUTO RIM loads for a long time, so by popular demand, here they are. Both loads are using high quality Starline brass. We've also incorporated a flash suppressed powder so you can shoot in the dark without blinding yourself and this is important because over 95% of all civilian shootings in the USA occur in low light when the criminal element is at work. Both of these loads are the equivalent of +P+ 45 ACP ammo or as it is also known, 45 Super. These are very stout loads, but will not harm modern 45 ACP revolvers, nor will these loads harm any post war 45 ACP revolvers. Feel free to safely shoot these loads in any post war 45 ACP revolver that is in normal good operating condition.

Check out the below velocities fired from personal real world revolvers, NOT test barrels. You'll notice that the new S&W 4 inch Mt. Gun gives speeds almost as fast as the older S&W revolvers with 5.5 and 6.5 inch barrels. This is NOT a typo. It simply shows that the new S&W revolvers are made to much tighter tolerances than the older S&W revolvers and therefore give higher velocities per inch of barrel. Also, we are aware that the 1937 manufactured model 1917 we used as a test gun, (see below velocity chart) is not post war.
Item # 32A - 255gr. hard cast flat nose bullet
S&W Mountain Gun, 4 inch bbl = 1031 FPS
S&W Model 325 (scandium) 2.5 inch bbl = 945 FPS
S&W model 1917 (1937 Production) 5.5 inch bbl = 1043 FPS
S&W 1955 Target (25-2) 6.5 inch bbl = 1070 FPS

Item # 32A - was designed for deep penetration with no bullet expansion. It will shoot right through stick frame and drywall construction walls and through both doors on a 2003 Dodge Ram or through a black bears skull, etc. It was designed for, among other things, outdoor use including black bear protection. Expect around 30 inches of penetration on live flesh and bone."

Tanfoglio pistols are manufactured by Fratelli Tanfoglio SpA. company, Italy. Basically, Force and Force 99 models are polymer frame versions of the Tanfoglio T95 Combat models, that, in turn, are clones of the famous CZ-75 design. The Force model was introduced in 1997, while the Force 99 model appeared two years later, in 1999.

Tanfoglio Force and Force 99 pistols are similar in design except for the new, redesigned frame of the Force 99. Both pistols are blowback operated, locked breech semi-auto pistols, that use browning hi-power style linkless system. Both models feature DA triggers with slide mounted safety / decock levers as well as internal firing pin block safety. New slide with slide-mounted safety/decocker lever (similar to T95 ) is available for Force 99 as a factory option. Both have fixed sights with three dots for increased visibility.

Tanfoglio polymer framed Force pistols are popular defensive and sporting firearms across the Europe. They also are imported into USA by EAA Corp. under the name ""Witness Polymer"" (Force) and ""Witness Polymer P"" (Force 99).

564,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1890564,For Sale:  NC Concealed Carry Handgun Class 7-27-2013,"Kings Mountain, Charlotte, North Carolina",$ 80,"Listed On: Monday, July 22, 2013",Services,no type,no type,no type,no type,"The North Carolina Concealed Carry Handgun Class requires that an individual that attends must meet several minimum standards as set forth by the North Carolina Administrative Code.
Those requirements are:
a) Course must be a minimum of eight (8) hours long plus range and qualification time.
b) The legal block of instruction must be a minimum of two (2) hours in length.
c) A written legal examination is required.

d) A shooting proficiency examination is required.  The course of fire must be a minimum of 30 rounds with 10 rounds fired from the three yard line, 10 rounds fired from the five yard line, and 10 rounds fired from the seven yard line.
e) The Concealed Carry Handgun Class must cover the following topics or it does not meet the minimum state standards:
*Legal Issues
*Handgun Safety
*Handguns
*Markmanship Fundamentals
*Carrying Concealed Safty Issues
*Presentation Techniques
*Cleaning and Maintenance
*Ammunition
*Proficiency Drills
PLEASE DO NOT BRING AMMUNITION  INTO THE CLASSROOM UNLESS INSTRUCTED TO DO SO BY THE INSTRUCTOR.
THE INSTRUCTOR RESERVES THE RIGHT TO INSPECT ALL FIREARMS FOR SAFETY AND PROPER OPERATION PRIOR TO THEIR USE.

The North Carolina Concealed Handgun Carry Permit Class is not difficult to complete.  The North Carolina Justice Academy designed this class for the average person, not just for those with lots of experience.  The range qualification shooting is fired from a distance of three, five and seven yards.  With our detailed instruction and guidance, shooters with very limited or no experience feel very comfortable and perform very well.

The cost of the Concealed Carry Handgun Class is $80.00 per person and will include: NC Concealed Carry Handgun Training handbook, materials, certificates, targets, range time, and lunch catered by 238 Cherokee Street Tavern.  Due to the cost of the state mandated materials and limited availability at class locations, pre-payment will secure your spot in the designated class in which you enroll.  All other students will be required to pay the day of class, providing that there are spots available.

Carolinas First Defense offers a unique an affordable CCW class that is not only a class, but an experience! Not only will you walk away with the knowledge, techniques, and skills it takes to apply for your Concealed Carry Permit, but you will also have the chance to win prizes throughout our class as well as enjoyed a catered lunch from a Kings Mountain restaurant. Throughout the class, we like to make it an enjoyable experience for all with group discussions, class volunteers, as well as raffles which gives those who attend the chance to win $25 Gas Gift Cards, $25 Retail Gift Cards, Carolinas First Defense T-shirts, gift cards to various local restaurants and businesses, as well as the Grand Prize which is a 3-day, 2 night vacation to over 36 select destinations domestic as well as international.

590,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1890590,For Sale:  S&W Gunsite Edition 1911PD Scandium frame 45 ACP,"Springdale, Fayetteville, Arkansas",$ 925,"Listed On: Monday, August 5, 2013",Handguns,Smith & Wesson                                                                                ,45 ACP                                                                                ,no type,Pistol,"This is the increasingly difficult to find Smith & Wesson 1911PD Gunsite Edition pistol.

The lusterous blueing on the slide, barrel and other hard parts is nicely contrasted by the lovely walnut stocks with the carved S&W and Gunsite Raven logo's which is echoed in the Raven engraving on the receiver. The frame is made from Scandium. The sights are Novak low rise and make for a smooth, no snag draw from a holster (no front gold bead). The barrel is 4 1/4"" with a match grade barrel bushing. The trigger is adjustable. The gun comes in the factory lockable protective case with the original manual, barrel wrench, 2 S&W OEM ACT made, 8 round magazines and sealed packet containing the sample factory fired casing.

I am the original owner and have fired this very accurate pistol less than 100 rounds of Federal and RP 45 ACP hardball. The earlier manufactured pistols like this one (SN FSP 0798) were completely hand fitted for maximum accuracy and reliability. The gun is in completely stock, unmodified condition since new. I will offer approximately 2 and 1/2 boxes of new RP (2 boxes of 50 rounds 230gr RN, approximately 1/2 box of Federal 230gr RN) to the buyer at my cost from about a year ago.
I play by the rules. For sale face to face only to bonafide Arkansas resident with proof of Ar residency, otherwise it has to go through (or sale to) an FFL.

I also believe in describing an item accurately. Feel free to check my feedback on ebay (handle- achildofthesky )I am an individual (no sales tax!) and not a dealer or business and because of this, the gun is sold with out warranties of any type on my part and all sales are final. That said, if you have been looking for a truely nice example of these accurate and finely assembled and increasingly hard to find pistols you will not be dissapointed with this one. I have a couple of other high quality collectable guns I will be selling to help generate funds for a home purchase.

Please note this offer expires on Friday evening as I am moving. Please, no ""tire kickers, Lookie Lou's or time wasters"", I am selling a exrtemely high quality,hand fitted handgun at a very attractive price. Not looking for trades unless you have a no lock S&W 340M&P 357 magnum scandium. You will NEVER see another one in this area. Don't miss out. Regret sucks!
Be safe and thanks for looking"

Of the six rigs, the IceMan is the only model to feature BowTech’s Center Pivot Technology and is one of two that use the new FLX Guard cable containment system. There are four, single-cam adult bows, one short draw bow and a youth model. The group features a wide range of axle-to-axle lengths, grip styles and limb angles. Other notable IceMan FLX features include a rotating module for easy draw-length adjustments, quiet InVelvet finish, stainless steel stabilizer-mounting insert and a String Stop.
FLX Tech

The 2010 IceMan FLX gets the last part of its name from the company’s new cable containment technology. Diamond’s FLX Guard uses a small, limb-like piece of material to attach a set of rollers to the riser. The material is like a bow limb in that it flexes during the draw cycle and shot. There is even a small limb pocket type fixture seated into a shallow cutout in the riser lined with a material that serves as the pivot point for the mini limb component, which we will call the FLX Limb for discussion purposes. The FLX Limb flexes toward the centerline of the bow during the draw cycle and then springs back into position and out of the way of the arrow when the string is released. Reaching back toward the shooter from where it is attached to the outside of the sight window, the FLX Limb curves inward toward the centerline of the bow. At the end closest to the shooter there is a fixture and set of two rollers attached with two small screws. When the FLX Guard moves toward the centerline of the bow, torque and tension applied to the cables is much reduced compared to a typical roller guard system. Rollers, of course, also reduce friction compared to a rod and slide cable guard. Lower friction, torque and tension results in an increase in the bow’s overall efficiency.
